PN,30501
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1778105470
OL,3,CAlaska mega-tsunami was second largest
OL,4,Cever recorded
OL,6,FA mega-tsunami triggered by a
OL,7,Fmountainside collapsing into an
OL,8,FAlaskan fjord last August has been
OL,9,Frevealed as the second-largest ever
OL,10,Frecorded.
OL,12,FA wave as high as the world's second-
OL,13,Fhighest building tore through the
OL,14,Flandscape around the Tracy Arm fjord,
OL,15,Fripping out trees and hurling millions
OL,16,Fof tonnes of rock in its path.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1778105470
OL,3,CAlaska mega-tsunami was second largest
OL,4,Cever recorded
OL,6,FIncredibly, no people or ships were
OL,7,Fnearby, despite Tracy Arm, a narrow
OL,8,Ffjord lined with steep mountains,
OL,9,Fwaterfalls and glaciers, being a
OL,10,Fpopular tourist destination.
OL,12,FIn the months since, a team of
OL,13,Fscientists from the US, Canada and
OL,14,FEurope has been studying the mega-
OL,15,Fwave, attempting to reconstruct what
OL,16,Fone researcher called a "hazard
OL,17,Fcascade." Their findings were
OL,18,Fpublished this week in the journal
OL,19,FScience.
OL,26,@xD@YOUyD@IO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1778105470
OL,3,CAlaska mega-tsunami was second largest
OL,4,Cever recorded
OL,6,FSuch was the scale of the Tracy Arm
OL,7,Fwave, which took just 45 seconds to a
OL,8,Fminute to wreak its destruction ` the
OL,9,Fmountainside that slid off to produce
OL,10,Fthe skyscraper-size wave alone was
OL,11,Fmore than 3,200 feet tall ` higher
OL,12,Fthan the world's tallest building,
OL,13,Feven scientists were in awe.
OL,15,FThe force of the tsunami was so great
OL,16,Fthat it generated seismic vibrations
OL,17,Fthat rippled across the planet, as
OL,18,Fenergy continued sloshing around the
OL,19,Ffjord for days after the initial
OL,20,Fcollapse.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1778105470
OL,3,CAlaska mega-tsunami was second largest
OL,4,Cever recorded
OL,6,FEven scientists used to natural
OL,7,Fphenomena were in awe of this mega-
OL,8,Fwave's power. To better understand and
OL,9,Fcommunicate its scale, scientists have
OL,10,Frecreated the event in a video game.
OL,12,FTsunami researcher Patrick Lynett said
OL,13,Fimmersing people in a virtual version
OL,14,Fof the disaster helps them grasp its
OL,15,Ftrue magnitude.
OL,17,F"If you can have them experience that
OL,18,Fdisaster digitally, they will recall
OL,19,Fit as something close to the real
OL,20,Fevent," Lynett said. "It's much better
OL,21,Fthan reading about it."
OL,26,@yD@AOU|D@GO]|D@VOU}D@WO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1778105470
OL,3,CAlaska mega-tsunami was second largest
OL,4,Cever recorded
OL,6,FThe video game shows the perspective
OL,7,Fof the landslide and tsunami wave from
OL,8,Fthe point of view of someone riding a
OL,9,Fjet ski trying to outrun a towering
OL,10,Fwall of water before quickly being
OL,11,Foverwhelmed by it.
OL,13,FLandslides are not uncommon in the
OL,14,FTracy Arm region, but scientists say
OL,15,Fclimate change is increasing both
OL,16,Ftheir frequency and intensity.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1778105470
OL,3,CAlaska mega-tsunami was second largest
OL,4,Cever recorded
OL,6,FAs glaciers retreat and ice melts,
OL,7,Fpreviously stable terrain is becoming
OL,8,Fincreasingly unstable that had been
OL,9,Fcovered for centuries, triggering
OL,10,Fevents such as the Aslankan tsunami.
OL,12,F"As the climate is changing, as
OL,13,Fglaciers are retreating, we are likely
OL,14,Fgoing to see more of these kinds of
OL,15,Fevents in high latitude environments
OL,16,Fin the Arctic and the sub-Arctic,"
OL,17,FShugar said.
OL,26,@tD@AOUxD@bO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1778105470
OL,3,CAlaska mega-tsunami was second largest
OL,4,Cever recorded
OL,6,FFor researchers, the goal is not just
OL,7,Fto understand what happened, but to
OL,8,Freduce the dangers, particularly for
OL,9,Fcoastal communities and tourists
OL,10,Fvisiting Alaska's fjords.
OL,12,F"As engineers, we can build things
OL,13,Freally strong, and we can make them
OL,14,Fsurvive the events," he said. "It's
OL,15,Fnot just how strong you can build
OL,16,Fthings, it's really training people
OL,17,Fhow to understand and react."
OL,26,@tD@AOUvD@TO]vD@_OUyD@]O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1778105470
OL,3,CAlaska mega-tsunami was second largest
OL,4,Cever recorded
OL,6,FScientists are also trying to
OL,7,Fdetermine why these massive landslides
OL,8,Fare becoming more common. Every piece
OL,9,Fof new information can help them try
OL,10,Fto reduce the risk going forward, when
OL,11,Fthe next one strikes, Daniel Shugar, a
OL,12,Fgeomorphologist and professor at the
OL,13,FUniversity of Calgary, said.
OL,15,F"I certainly hope that we don't get a
OL,16,Frepeat event this summer, but it's
OL,17,Fentirely possible," he said. "As
OL,18,Fhazard scientists, as disaster
OL,19,Fscientists, we want to minimize the
OL,20,Frisk to people and infrastructure from
OL,21,Fthese events."
OL,26,@wD@AOUyD@SO]yD@^OU}D@NO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
